<i>(LIPSYTE) That was kind of his
Declaration of Independence.</i>

437
00:26:27,453 --> 00:26:31,288
This is complete freedom, not just a
cup of coffee or a seat in a school...

438
00:26:31,290 --> 00:26:34,058
or a token... This is real.

439
00:26:36,027 --> 00:26:41,031
The Honorable Elijah Muhammad say he was
too big of a man to carry that "X"...

440
00:26:41,033 --> 00:26:44,101
and named him Muhammad Ali.

441
00:26:44,369 --> 00:26:47,204
I remember the exact moment
we told my dad and mom.

442
00:26:47,206 --> 00:26:51,909
We said, "The Honorable Elijah
Muhammad gave us our name".

443
00:26:51,911 --> 00:26:53,277
They became very angry.

444
00:26:53,279 --> 00:26:55,045
They said, "What in the
world do you mean?"

445
00:26:55,047 --> 00:27:01,051
<i>My brother said, "Dad, I'm Muhammad
Ali." You got to accept it.</i>

446
00:27:01,053 --> 00:27:01,919
(MAN)
What does it mean?

447
00:27:01,921 --> 00:27:07,124
"Muhammad" means "worthy of all
praises" and "Ali" means "most high."

448
00:27:08,026 --> 00:27:12,262
<i>(LIPSYTE) At theNew York
Times, the top editor felt...</i>

449
00:27:12,264 --> 00:27:13,330
we met you as Cassius Clay.

450
00:27:13,332 --> 00:27:19,403
Until you go into a court of law and
change your name, you are Cassius Clay.

451
00:27:19,405 --> 00:27:21,105
<i>And it really kind
of bothered me.</i>

452
00:27:21,107 --> 00:27:24,875
Nobody asked John Wayne or Rock
Hudson what their names were.

453
00:27:24,877 --> 00:27:27,444
<i>But I tried to slip
it in when I could.</i>

454
00:27:27,446 --> 00:27:33,217
<i>I usually ended up writing "Muhammad
Ali, a.k.a. Cassius Clay."</i>

455
00:27:33,219 --> 00:27:36,353
His change of name,
what did it threaten?

456
00:27:36,355 --> 00:27:40,357
If he was white, they would be referring
to him as the All-American boy.

457
00:27:40,359 --> 00:27:42,526
<i>(MUWAKKIL) It was an
affront to many Americans...</i>

458
00:27:42,528 --> 00:27:44,428
<i>that the heavyweight
champion of the world...</i>

459
00:27:44,430 --> 00:27:47,898
would reject American identity
and all of that entails...

460
00:27:47,900 --> 00:27:52,102
for something as obscure and
cultish as the Nation of Islam.

461
00:27:52,104 --> 00:27:55,039
- (MAN) Cassius, you're...
- I'm not Cassius. You still calling me...

462
00:27:55,041 --> 00:27:58,509
- Or Muhammad, you're talking...
- I'm not no white man.

463
00:27:58,511 --> 00:28:02,046
So you want to keep calling me a
white man's name. I'm not white.

464
00:28:02,048 --> 00:28:04,682
I don't want to be called
after your name no more.

465
00:28:04,684 --> 00:28:08,285
I'm not no slave.
I'm Muhammad Ali.

466
00:28:12,786 --> 00:28:15,626
<i>(KHALILAH) I was
working in the bakery...</i>

467
00:28:15,628 --> 00:28:19,296
and he would go in
and he would say,

468
00:28:19,298 --> 00:28:23,600
"I know your name.
I know your name."

469
00:28:25,570 --> 00:28:28,972
And I'd say, "Well,
whoop-de-do." I says that.

470
00:28:28,974 --> 00:28:35,512
He says, "And I got a name of culture
now. My name is Muhammad Ali."

471
00:28:38,450 --> 00:28:39,983
<i>(CROWD CHEERING)</i>

472
00:28:39,985 --> 00:28:43,153
Now that he gave me the beautiful
name of Muhammad Ali...

473
00:28:43,155 --> 00:28:45,989
and took away that slave
name of Cassius Clay,

474
00:28:45,991 --> 00:28:47,624
now I can go all over the world.

475
00:28:47,626 --> 00:28:51,662
- All over the world!
- (CROWD CHEERING, APPLAUDING)

476
00:28:52,263 --> 00:28:56,934
Muslims all over the world who
never followed boxing said,

477
00:28:56,936 --> 00:28:58,402
"Ooh! Look."

478
00:28:58,404 --> 00:29:05,042
There's a Muslim in America
named Muhammad Ali.

479
00:29:05,044 --> 00:29:10,214
<i>Those are big, big names
in the Islamic world.</i>

480
00:29:10,715 --> 00:29:15,052
His international
appeal, it was vast.

481
00:29:15,054 --> 00:29:15,519
Welcome.

482
00:29:15,521 --> 00:29:18,522
The young people of Ghana
want to welcome you.

483
00:29:18,524 --> 00:29:21,625
<i>(ALI) Ghana, Nigeria,
Pakistan and Turkey,</i>

484
00:29:21,627 --> 00:29:25,062
<i>they call me their
champion too.</i>

485
00:29:25,518 --> 00:29:28,398
I was surprised. The whole
world was watching it.

486
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:31,001
- (MAN) They sure were.
- Yeah.

487
00:29:43,110 --> 00:29:46,150
<i>(MAN) What kind of impression
do you try to leave...</i>

488
00:29:46,152 --> 00:29:47,684
<i>on the nations you
visit over there?</i>

489
00:29:47,686 --> 00:29:53,090
<i>(MUHAMMAD ALI) Well, uh,
just as a clean-living Muslim.</i>

490
00:29:53,092 --> 00:29:57,227
<i>Letting them know they have hundreds and
thousands of brothers here in America.</i>

491
00:29:57,229 --> 00:29:59,797
All of these are Muslim
countries that I've been to.

492
00:29:59,799 --> 00:30:01,698
He's in a better position
than anyone else...

493
00:30:01,700 --> 00:30:06,336
to restore the racial pride to not
only our people in this country,

494
00:30:06,338 --> 00:30:07,571
but all over the world.

495
00:30:07,573 --> 00:30:11,241
- (APPLAUDING)
- <i> As-salaam alaikum.</i>

496
00:30:11,243 --> 00:30:14,244
(ALI) I've been all over into
the deepest parts of Africa...

497
00:30:14,246 --> 00:30:20,150
and Egypt, and everybody knows and are
talking about the Muslims in America.

498
00:30:20,152 --> 00:30:22,686
- Everybody.
- (APPLAUDING)

499
00:30:23,121 --> 00:30:27,658
And if it was not for the teachings
of the Honorable Elijah Muhammad...

500
00:30:27,660 --> 00:30:30,093
not bragging, but a
man in my position...

501
00:30:30,095 --> 00:30:33,230
that would be the last place I
would go is Africa and Egypt.

502
00:30:33,232 --> 00:30:38,569
The first stop would have been Paris,
London, France, like the rest of them.

503
00:30:38,571 --> 00:30:41,538
(CHEERING, APPLAUDING)

504
00:30:46,644 --> 00:30:51,348
<i>(DAVIDSON) He hired Elijah
Muhammad's son to be his "manager."</i>

505
00:30:51,350 --> 00:30:54,240
But it was very clear that
he didn't really mean

506
00:30:54,253 --> 00:30:57,154
manager like the Louisville
Sponsoring Group.

507
00:30:57,156 --> 00:30:58,755
How many managers do you have?

508
00:30:58,757 --> 00:31:03,093
Oh, I have 11 backers. I
don't... I have one manager.

509
00:31:03,095 --> 00:31:04,194
<i>(DAVIDSON)</i>
<i>They flattered him.</i>

510
00:31:04,196 --> 00:31:10,200
They treated him as a very important
person, which, of course, he was.

511
00:31:10,202 --> 00:31:12,336
<i>They made him a hero.</i>

512
00:31:12,338 --> 00:31:13,570
<i>He didn't live in
Louisville anymore.</i>

513
00:31:13,572 --> 00:31:18,475
<i>But he was never introduced as anything
except from Louisville, Kentucky.</i>

514
00:31:18,477 --> 00:31:23,347
To a boxer, that's not a small
thing, how you're announced.

515
00:31:23,349 --> 00:31:29,086
<i>Ali kept his word on every
fight that we made for him.</i>

516
00:31:29,088 --> 00:31:35,926
<i>And he never argued about black
or white problems with us.</i>

517
00:31:35,928 --> 00:31:38,161
<i>I think Ali probably
told the Muslims</i>

518
00:31:38,163 --> 00:31:42,065
<i>don't mess with the
Louisville Sponsoring Group.</i>

519
00:31:42,067 --> 00:31:44,434
<i>Leave them alone.</i>

520
00:31:45,403 --> 00:31:49,806
I understand that you're headed
to meet with Elijah Muhammad.

521
00:31:49,808 --> 00:31:52,609
- Yes, Sir. Having dinner
with him. - Uh-huh.

522
00:31:52,611 --> 00:31:55,846
One of the main reasons is your
friendship with Malcolm X.

523
00:31:55,848 --> 00:31:59,483
- He's a friend of yours now, isn't
he? - Yeah. He is a brother of mine.

524
00:31:59,485 --> 00:32:02,519
- He's my brother. Whatever he
do, he's my brother. - Uh-huh.

525
00:32:02,521 --> 00:32:03,620
Now that he's split
away from the...

526
00:32:03,622 --> 00:32:07,758
I don't know about splitting. I'll have
to see the higher authority on that.

527
00:32:07,760 --> 00:32:09,793
(MAN) There's been great
publicity given to the fact...

528
00:32:09,795 --> 00:32:13,330
that heavyweight champion Cassius
Clay is one of your followers.

529
00:32:13,332 --> 00:32:15,632
Well, Cassius is following
Elijah Muhammad.

530
00:32:15,634 --> 00:32:21,838
And, uh, I'm no longer a follower
of Elijah Muhammad myself.

531
00:32:21,840 --> 00:32:23,907
<i>And I think that the
black Muslim movement,</i>

532
00:32:23,909 --> 00:32:27,711
if it doesn't adopt the
Sunni practice of Islam,

533
00:32:27,713 --> 00:32:30,614
that it will disintegrate
and fall apart.

534
00:32:30,616 --> 00:32:33,517
There's no organization
in this country...

535
00:32:33,519 --> 00:32:36,954
that could do more for the
struggling black man...

536
00:32:36,956 --> 00:32:40,757
than the black Muslim
movement if it wanted to.

537
00:32:40,759 --> 00:32:43,560
But it has gotten into
the possession...

538
00:32:43,562 --> 00:32:45,429
of a man who's become senile,

539
00:32:45,431 --> 00:32:48,732
<i>and then he has surrounded
himself by his children...</i>

540
00:32:48,734 --> 00:32:52,369
<i>who are now in power and
want nothing but luxury...</i>

541
00:32:52,371 --> 00:32:55,472
and will do anything to
safeguard their own interests.

542
00:32:55,474 --> 00:33:02,713
People like myself and Ali, we
were in the valley of decision.

543
00:33:02,715 --> 00:33:06,717
Should I follow a man
that taught me...

544
00:33:06,719 --> 00:33:11,788
or should I follow the teacher
of the man who taught me?

545
00:33:11,790 --> 00:33:14,691
Elijah Muhammad called
all of his officials...

546
00:33:14,693 --> 00:33:17,594
national officials to
Chicago in October...

547
00:33:17,596 --> 00:33:23,367
and ordered them to kill or
maim any of his followers...

548
00:33:23,369 --> 00:33:25,736
who leave him to follow me.

549
00:33:25,738 --> 00:33:28,005
Does this split disturb
you that's been reported?

550
00:33:28,007 --> 00:33:32,175
No. What Malcolm X does is
his business. He's one man.

551
00:33:32,343 --> 00:33:37,881
<i>(MUWAKKIL) Muhammad Ali chose to go
with the establishment, so to speak.</i>

552
00:33:37,883 --> 00:33:42,819
<i>(MAN) Elijah Muhammad has given
his blessing to a new recruiter...</i>

553
00:33:42,821 --> 00:33:45,355
<i>Cassius Muhammad Ali Clay.</i>

554
00:33:45,357 --> 00:33:48,592
(ALL)
We are the greatest!

555
00:33:48,594 --> 00:33:50,494
<i>(MAN)</i>
<i>Clay is no Malcolm X,</i>

556
00:33:50,496 --> 00:33:54,531
<i>but he has become an
idol for youngsters.</i>

557
00:33:54,699 --> 00:33:57,300
<i>(MUWAKKIL) A lot of Malcolmites
who were following Malcolm...</i>

558
00:33:57,302 --> 00:34:00,604
<i>were really not equally attracted
to the Nation of Islam.</i>

559
00:34:00,606 --> 00:34:04,307
<i>They were attracted to Malcolm's
audacity, his eloquence...</i>

560
00:34:04,309 --> 00:34:06,532
and his vision,
which, in some ways,

561
00:34:06,545 --> 00:34:08,779
elaborated the vision
of the Nation of Islam.

562
00:34:08,781 --> 00:34:13,850
I pray that God will bless you
in everything that you do.

563
00:34:14,352 --> 00:34:17,888
I pray that you will
grow intellectually...

564
00:34:17,890 --> 00:34:20,690
so that you can understand
the problems of the world...

565
00:34:20,692 --> 00:34:24,928
and where you fit into
in that world picture.

566
00:34:32,804 --> 00:34:34,071
(SIREN WAILING)

567
00:34:34,073 --> 00:34:36,940
<i>(MAN) He's a hero to me. He
stood out among all black people.</i>

568
00:34:36,942 --> 00:34:38,442
He showed the white
man where it was at.

569
00:34:38,444 --> 00:34:40,710
(MAN) Who do you believe is
responsible for Malcolm X's death?

570
00:34:40,712 --> 00:34:41,912
The white power structure
is America is behind it.

571
00:34:41,914 --> 00:34:46,950
And they're quick to capitalize on it by
saying that one of his own kind did it.

572
00:34:46,952 --> 00:34:49,586
But they put it up to be done.

573
00:34:54,725 --> 00:34:59,863
Now, I give him credit for the good work he
done when he was with the Nation of Islam.

574
00:34:59,865 --> 00:35:02,365
We didn't have nobody better.

575
00:35:02,934 --> 00:35:06,203
<i>But Elijah Muhammad made him.</i>

576
00:35:06,457 --> 00:35:07,737
<i>When Malcolm was a good man...</i>

577
00:35:07,739 --> 00:35:10,740
<i>preaching the teachings of the
Honorable Elijah Muhammad,</i>

578
00:35:10,742 --> 00:35:13,477
<i>I would have gave
my life for him.</i>

579
00:35:13,479 --> 00:35:15,579
<i>But when he turned
viciously...</i>

580
00:35:15,581 --> 00:35:17,747
against the Honorable
Elijah Muhammad,

581
00:35:17,749 --> 00:35:21,618
if I could have got ahold of him,
I might have killed him myself.

582
00:35:21,620 --> 00:35:23,553
But we didn't kill him.
'Cause you know why?

583
00:35:23,555 --> 00:35:25,989
Because we took orders from the
Honorable Elijah Muhammad.

584
00:35:25,991 --> 00:35:28,758
He told us not to touch him.
Let him just go.

585
00:35:28,760 --> 00:35:33,029
Malcolm is the victim
of his own preaching.

586
00:35:33,031 --> 00:35:35,765
He preached violence, and so
he become the victim of it.

587
00:35:35,767 --> 00:35:39,636
<i>(RAHAMAN) So many things have
been said wrong about Malcolm X.</i>

588
00:35:39,638 --> 00:35:44,474
Malcolm X was a
very nice person.

589
00:35:44,542 --> 00:35:48,812
<i>The Bible says "He without
sin cast the first Stone."</i>

590
00:35:48,814 --> 00:35:50,580
<i>That's a strong statement.</i>

591
00:35:50,582 --> 00:35:52,682
(SIRENS WAILING)

592
00:35:52,684 --> 00:35:53,950
<i>(RADIO DISPATCHER,</I>
<I>INDISTINCT)</i>

593
00:35:53,952 --> 00:35:56,686
<i>(LIPSYTE) The night that
Malcolm X was killed,</i>

594
00:35:56,688 --> 00:36:01,391
<i>there was a fire in
Ali's apartment.</i>

595
00:36:02,026 --> 00:36:05,829
<i>The implication was
that it was arson.</i>

596
00:36:06,464 --> 00:36:09,666
<i>That it was some
sort of revenge.</i>

597
00:36:09,668 --> 00:36:10,934
<i>Uh, I don't know.</i>

598
00:36:10,936 --> 00:36:16,940
<i>I think there's no question that Ali
had to have been scared himself.</i>

599
00:36:16,942 --> 00:36:18,909
<i>Malcolm, in many ways,</i>

600
00:36:18,911 --> 00:36:23,146
<i>was a more important political
figure than Muhammad Ali.</i>

601
00:36:23,148 --> 00:36:29,553
I mean, if you could waste him,
you could certainly waste Ali.

602
00:36:29,555 --> 00:36:31,888
<i>He was still just a boxer.</i>

603
00:36:31,890 --> 00:36:37,127
I feel for his life because the
condition the world is in today.

604
00:36:37,129 --> 00:36:40,163
And, uh, you never know
what's going to happen...

605
00:36:40,165 --> 00:36:42,165
when you're in public
life like he is.

606
00:36:42,167 --> 00:36:47,137
And I'm much concerned about the
fire that started in his apartment.

607
00:36:47,139 --> 00:36:50,907
And I do wish that he would
withdraw from this movement...

608
00:36:50,909 --> 00:36:54,010
because I am awful
worried about him.

609
00:36:54,012 --> 00:36:56,046
We raised him to
be a Christian...

610
00:36:56,048 --> 00:36:59,883
and took him to church every
Sunday when he was small...

611
00:36:59,885 --> 00:37:04,187
on up till he got out, you
know, in the world on his own.

612
00:37:04,189 --> 00:37:08,225
And then he got in this organization
which we do not approve of at all.

613
00:37:08,227 --> 00:37:11,661
(MAN) Your mother was quoted
yesterday in Louisville as saying...

614
00:37:11,663 --> 00:37:13,096
that she felt you ought to
leave the Muslim movement.

615
00:37:13,098 --> 00:37:16,499
- How do you feel about... - It's natural
for a mother to be worried about her son...

616
00:37:16,501 --> 00:37:20,537
with the press writing all of these
things about somebody's life's in danger.

617
00:37:20,539 --> 00:37:21,871
You know how the press
can blow things up...

618
00:37:21,873 --> 00:37:25,275
and make it look like we in a
war with some black people.

619
00:37:25,277 --> 00:37:27,744
We not at war with nobody.

620
00:37:27,812 --> 00:37:30,513
<i>(ALI) And I'm walking the
streets daily by myself.</i>

621
00:37:30,515 --> 00:37:34,217
<i>And, uh, if anybody want
me, they can find me.</i>

622
00:37:34,219 --> 00:37:38,121
Malcolm X and anybody
else who attacks, uh...

623
00:37:38,123 --> 00:37:41,258
talks about attacking
Elijah Muhammad will die.

624
00:37:41,260 --> 00:37:48,265
No man can oppose the message of Almighty
God, uh, verbally or physically...

625
00:37:48,267 --> 00:37:50,700
and get away with it.

626
00:37:58,709 --> 00:38:05,282
Floyd Patterson didn't think that there
should be a Muslim heavyweight champion.

627
00:38:05,284 --> 00:38:10,020
Refused to call Ali
by his new name.

628
00:38:10,022 --> 00:38:12,922
<i>(PATTERSON) Cassius Clay
doesn't fully understand...</i>

629
00:38:12,924 --> 00:38:16,126
<i>what the black
Muslim stands for.</i>

630
00:38:16,994 --> 00:38:19,029
<i>It's like the Ku Klux Klan.</i>

631
00:38:19,031 --> 00:38:23,566
<i>I think that hurts the
championship quite a bit.</i>

632
00:38:25,965 --> 00:38:29,005
<i>(ALI) Oh, I'm gonna have
to give him a good whipping.</i>

633
00:38:29,007 --> 00:38:35,712
And I have entitled it "A Floyd
Patterson Humiliation Punishment."

634
00:38:42,053 --> 00:38:44,587
- (BELL RINGS)
- (CHEERING)

635
00:38:44,689 --> 00:38:47,190
<i>(MUWAKKIL) Floyd was kind
of a hero to us at one point.</i>

636
00:38:47,192 --> 00:38:50,960
You know, a black heavyweight champion is
always a big hit in the black community.

637
00:38:50,962 --> 00:38:54,964
But when he came up
against Muhammad Ali,

638
00:38:54,966 --> 00:38:57,267
<i>he was fighting the
fight of America...</i>

639
00:38:57,269 --> 00:39:00,737
<i>doing the job of slaying
the militant Negro.</i>

640
00:39:00,739 --> 00:39:02,906
<i>(LIPSYTE) I was at the
Floyd Patterson fight.</i>

641
00:39:02,908 --> 00:39:07,177
The man was bent over like
somebody with osteoporosis.

642
00:39:07,179 --> 00:39:12,649
<i>He couldn't really defend himself.
The fight should have been stopped.</i>

643
00:39:12,651 --> 00:39:16,720
<i>One or two good combinations
and he'd be gone.</i>

644
00:39:16,722 --> 00:39:22,058
<i>I think he carried Floyd Patterson just
so that he could inflict the punishment.</i>

645
00:39:22,060 --> 00:39:26,763
<i>(ANNOUNCER) The champion
continues to be on target.</i>

646
00:39:27,498 --> 00:39:29,733
<i>(LIPSYTE)</i>
<i>It was disgusting.</i>

647
00:39:29,735 --> 00:39:33,169
<i>(MUWAKKIL) Muhammad Ali had
prolonged the punishment...</i>

648
00:39:33,171 --> 00:39:36,172
<i>to make sure Patterson
understood his offense.</i>

649
00:39:36,174 --> 00:39:39,809
It perfectly harmonized with our
feelings about Floyd Patterson.

