Simple as that.

1089
01:04:22,758 --> 01:04:26,194
<i>(ANNOUNCER) The United States leads
the Olympics in medal awards...</i>

1090
01:04:26,196 --> 01:04:28,797
<i>and is just about supreme
in the sprint races,</i>

1091
01:04:28,799 --> 01:04:32,267
<i>thanks to men like Tommie
Smith and John Carlos.</i>

1092
01:04:32,269 --> 01:04:35,303
<i>They came in first and third.</i>

1093
01:04:35,305 --> 01:04:38,340
<i>(CARLOS) Any time they
have an Olympic Games...</i>

1094
01:04:38,342 --> 01:04:41,810
or any time they do a national
anthem at a football game,

1095
01:04:41,812 --> 01:04:43,144
that's politics right there.

1096
01:04:43,146 --> 01:04:45,780
<i>We felt that as young
individual athletes...</i>

1097
01:04:45,782 --> 01:04:49,517
<i>that we could make a significant
difference in society.</i>

1098
01:04:49,519 --> 01:04:52,687
<i>I said, "Look, Tommie, I
wanna make a statement."</i>

1099
01:04:52,689 --> 01:04:56,992
<i>♪ (Star-Spangled Banner)</i>

1100
01:04:56,994 --> 01:05:01,162
"Let's put a black glove on and say
although we're proud to be Americans,

1101
01:05:01,164 --> 01:05:03,665
we're prouder to be
black Americans."

1102
01:05:03,667 --> 01:05:06,735
<i>I had a black shirt on
to cover up my U.S.A...</i>

1103
01:05:06,737 --> 01:05:08,536
<i>because I was ashamed
of America...</i>

1104
01:05:08,538 --> 01:05:11,840
<i>the way America has
been all these years.</i>

1105
01:05:11,842 --> 01:05:13,475
We have a great history
in this country.

1106
01:05:13,477 --> 01:05:17,712
But at the same time, we have a
history that we should be ashamed of.

1107
01:05:17,714 --> 01:05:19,381
<i>The number-one statement
in my mind...</i>

1108
01:05:19,383 --> 01:05:24,719
was to have Muhammad Ali vindicated
from all the nonsense, negativities...

1109
01:05:24,721 --> 01:05:26,254
that they try and
put around him...

1110
01:05:26,256 --> 01:05:29,157
and give him the right to be
the champion that he deserve.

1111
01:05:29,159 --> 01:05:31,693
<i>(CARMICHAEL) Wanna let
the whole world know...</i>

1112
01:05:31,695 --> 01:05:35,530
that we are going to pick
our heroes from today on.

1113
01:05:35,532 --> 01:05:38,366
And brother Tommie Smith,
brother John Carlos...

1114
01:05:38,368 --> 01:05:39,634
join the rank of brother
Muhammad Ali...

1115
01:05:39,636 --> 01:05:42,076
because we want black
people who are concerned

1116
01:05:42,089 --> 01:05:44,539
with us first and
with sports second.

1117
01:05:44,541 --> 01:05:46,541
- Yeah!
- (WOMAN) Yea!

1118
01:05:46,543 --> 01:05:49,678
When you refused
to be drafted,

1119
01:05:49,680 --> 01:05:52,347
do you think that it set
a Mark in history...

1120
01:05:52,349 --> 01:05:54,849
as one black person who just
out and out refused to...

1121
01:05:54,851 --> 01:05:57,786
Many have done it before me, but
they were not famous cases.

1122
01:05:57,788 --> 01:06:02,290
And I just don't think I should
go 10,000 miles from here...

1123
01:06:02,292 --> 01:06:04,559
and shoot some black people
who never called me "nigger,"

1124
01:06:04,561 --> 01:06:06,795
never lynched me,
never put dogs on me,

1125
01:06:06,797 --> 01:06:08,964
never raped my mama,
enslaved me...

1126
01:06:08,966 --> 01:06:12,400
and deprived me of freedom,
justice and equality.

1127
01:06:12,402 --> 01:06:14,569
And he's black too. I
just can't shoot him.

1128
01:06:14,571 --> 01:06:18,239
And with this in mind, and
plus my religious beliefs too,

1129
01:06:18,241 --> 01:06:20,408
which is the legal
reason I'm not going,

1130
01:06:20,410 --> 01:06:23,445
I just can't go over there
and shoot them people...

1131
01:06:23,447 --> 01:06:26,581
and come back home
I'm still a nigger.

1132
01:06:26,583 --> 01:06:31,319
It has been said that I
have two alternatives...

1133
01:06:31,321 --> 01:06:35,423
either go to jail
or go to the army.

1134
01:06:35,425 --> 01:06:39,594
But I would like to say that
there is another alternative.

1135
01:06:39,596 --> 01:06:44,432
And that alternative
is justice.

1136
01:06:51,502 --> 01:06:54,342
<i>(MAN) I came to work
for Justice Harlan...</i>

1137
01:06:54,344 --> 01:06:57,812
<i>in the summer of 1970,</i>

1138
01:06:57,814 --> 01:06:59,781
<i>which during the
term I was there...</i>

1139
01:06:59,783 --> 01:07:02,283
<i>that the Vietnam Veterans
Against the War...</i>

1140
01:07:02,285 --> 01:07:05,320
<i>sat in on the steps
of the Supreme Court.</i>

1141
01:07:05,322 --> 01:07:07,489
(CHANTING)
No!

1142
01:07:08,657 --> 01:07:11,659
(CHANTING, INDISTINCT)

1143
01:07:11,661 --> 01:07:13,661
<i>There was controversy...</i>

1144
01:07:13,663 --> 01:07:17,365
just surrounding every
corner of life.

1145
01:07:17,367 --> 01:07:22,570
- Black Power!
- (SHOUTING, INDISTINCT)

1146
01:07:22,572 --> 01:07:25,473
Ship all niggers back!

1147
01:07:26,575 --> 01:07:30,512
It was during that year that
Clay against United States...

1148
01:07:30,514 --> 01:07:31,780
<i>came up to the Supreme Court.</i>

1149
01:07:31,782 --> 01:07:36,451
<i>The justices probably
thought Ali wouldn't win.</i>

1150
01:07:36,453 --> 01:07:39,754
He could argue about it, but
he had a fair shot below...

1151
01:07:39,756 --> 01:07:41,756
when reasonable
judges had said no.

1152
01:07:41,758 --> 01:07:44,959
And he didn't present any
unique or unusual issues,

1153
01:07:44,961 --> 01:07:47,495
and so they were just gonna
let the case go away.

1154
01:07:47,497 --> 01:07:49,264
<i>As they were about
to announce,</i>

1155
01:07:49,266 --> 01:07:51,032
<i>the solicitor general
came in and said...</i>

1156
01:07:51,034 --> 01:07:54,069
we just learned that there
was an illegal wiretap...

1157
01:07:54,071 --> 01:08:00,775
during which the F.B.I. overheard Muhammad
Ali talking to Reverend Martin Luther King.

1158
01:08:00,777 --> 01:08:04,612
We are all victims of the
same system of oppression.

1159
01:08:04,614 --> 01:08:08,983
And even though we may have
different religious beliefs,

1160
01:08:08,985 --> 01:08:13,755
this does not at all bring about a
difference in terms of our concerns.

1161
01:08:13,757 --> 01:08:15,857
We're still brothers.

1162
01:08:16,092 --> 01:08:18,860
<i>(KRATTENMAKER) So they just did
what was routine in those days.</i>

1163
01:08:18,862 --> 01:08:21,596
<i>We're sending this back
down to the trial judge...</i>

1164
01:08:21,598 --> 01:08:24,732
<i>to determine whether
anything needs to be done.</i>

1165
01:08:24,734 --> 01:08:29,003
I didn't think it would take so
long... three and a half years...

1166
01:08:29,005 --> 01:08:30,905
but I did think
he would be back.

1167
01:08:30,907 --> 01:08:33,641
<i>And he was always doing
something interesting.</i>

1168
01:08:33,643 --> 01:08:36,911
He was in a Broadway show,
Big Time Buck White.

1169
01:08:36,913 --> 01:08:41,182
- (APPLAUSE)
- <i> It was wonderful and terrible</i>.

1170
01:08:46,889 --> 01:08:51,392
You know, I first came here
some 400 long years ago.

1171
01:08:51,394 --> 01:08:52,494
Yes. Right on, Big Time.

1172
01:08:52,496 --> 01:08:55,730
- I came as a first-class
passenger... - Yes!

1173
01:08:55,732 --> 01:09:00,435
On a cold, nasty, muddy,
wet prison of death.

1174
01:09:00,437 --> 01:09:03,705
- Yes! Yes!
- A slave ship.

1175
01:09:03,707 --> 01:09:06,374
♪ We came in chains ♪

1176
01:09:06,376 --> 01:09:07,142
Yeah!

1177
01:09:07,144 --> 01:09:09,878
- ♪ We came in misery ♪
- Uh-huh.

1178
01:09:09,880 --> 01:09:15,650
♪ Now all our suffering and
pains are part of history ♪

1179
01:09:15,652 --> 01:09:16,618
Right on!

1180
01:09:16,620 --> 01:09:18,319
- ♪ We came in chains ♪
- Oh, yes!

1181
01:09:18,321 --> 01:09:21,189
<i>(MAN) Do you feel in a way that
you're not really acting up there?</i>

1182
01:09:21,191 --> 01:09:23,725
No, I'm not acting at all.
I'm real.

1183
01:09:23,727 --> 01:09:25,160
We may have a little
music in the background,

1184
01:09:25,162 --> 01:09:28,696
but everything that I do, I
look at it as being real.

1185
01:09:28,698 --> 01:09:30,732
♪ Chains, chains, chains ♪

1186
01:09:30,734 --> 01:09:32,400
♪ We came in chains ♪

1187
01:09:32,402 --> 01:09:33,568
♪ Four hundred years ♪

1188
01:09:33,570 --> 01:09:36,171
♪ No justice No
freedom No equality ♪

1189
01:09:36,173 --> 01:09:38,506
♪ Worked from sunup
to sundown ♪

1190
01:09:38,508 --> 01:09:40,608
♪ 1970, still in chains ♪

1191
01:09:40,610 --> 01:09:43,611
♪ Financial chains
Economical chains ♪

1192
01:09:43,613 --> 01:09:45,480
♪ Chains, chains, chains ♪

1193
01:09:45,482 --> 01:09:47,081
♪ America chains ♪

1194
01:09:47,083 --> 01:09:50,485
♪ Chains Look at
these chains ♪

1195
01:09:50,487 --> 01:09:51,953
♪ Chains ♪

1196
01:09:51,955 --> 01:09:54,622
♪ Chains ♪

1197
01:09:54,624 --> 01:09:57,792
♪ Chains ♪

1198
01:09:57,794 --> 01:10:00,862
(CHEERING)

1199
01:10:02,559 --> 01:10:05,800
<i>(ANNOUNCER) Meanwhile, a group
of Atlanta blacks and whites...</i>

1200
01:10:05,802 --> 01:10:09,904
<i>managed to get Clay a license
and bring the fight to Atlanta.</i>

1201
01:10:09,906 --> 01:10:12,207
No other city has done this.

1202
01:10:12,209 --> 01:10:18,012
We put Mr. Clay, Muhammad
Ali, back into the ring.

1203
01:10:18,607 --> 01:10:20,848
<i>I don't see how this fight
could take place...</i>

1204
01:10:20,850 --> 01:10:22,483
anywhere in the United
States of America...

1205
01:10:22,485 --> 01:10:26,621
<i>by a man that has denounced
his country's uniform...</i>

1206
01:10:26,623 --> 01:10:29,090
<i>and refused to be inducted.</i>

1207
01:10:29,658 --> 01:10:32,527
There are no state
laws in Georgia...

1208
01:10:32,529 --> 01:10:33,228
covering the boxing industry.

1209
01:10:33,230 --> 01:10:39,133
<i>We have secured from the city of Atlanta
the boxing permit, the license.</i>

1210
01:10:39,135 --> 01:10:41,202
<i>We've covered everything.</i>

1211
01:10:41,204 --> 01:10:44,472
Muhammad Ali, or Cassius
Clay, or both...

1212
01:10:44,474 --> 01:10:47,175
will return to the boxing
ring in Atlanta, Georgia.

1213
01:10:47,177 --> 01:10:49,711
<i>Governor Maddox
does not like it.</i>

1214
01:10:49,713 --> 01:10:50,712
But he can't stop it.

1215
01:10:50,714 --> 01:10:52,714
I've called for a day of
mourning because of this,

1216
01:10:52,716 --> 01:10:56,251
that this tragic thing has happened
in this United States of America...

1217
01:10:56,253 --> 01:11:00,855
where men have fought so long and their
wives and children have sacrificed so much.

1218
01:11:00,857 --> 01:11:04,993
<i>(ANNOUNCER) But there are a lot of
people who feel as Governor Maddox does.</i>

1219
01:11:04,995 --> 01:11:08,496
<i>But Clay has his license
and will fight.</i>

1220
01:11:08,498 --> 01:11:10,765
Your greatest trial may
not be in the ring.

1221
01:11:10,767 --> 01:11:11,799
It may be with the
American public,

1222
01:11:11,801 --> 01:11:17,639
most of whom deeply resent your stance
with regard to military induction.

1223
01:11:18,207 --> 01:11:21,509
<i>(KRATTENMAKER) Because Ali was
such a visible public figure,</i>

1224
01:11:21,511 --> 01:11:26,714
<i>Justice Brennan thought we just
can't let a case like this go...</i>

1225
01:11:26,716 --> 01:11:27,915
without explaining why.

1226
01:11:27,917 --> 01:11:30,618
<i>So we caught the case
on the bounce back.</i>

1227
01:11:30,620 --> 01:11:33,260
The Supreme Court
agreed today to review

1228
01:11:33,273 --> 01:11:35,923
heavyweight fighter Muhammad
Ali's conviction...

1229
01:11:35,925 --> 01:11:37,692
for refusing induction
into the army.

1230
01:11:37,694 --> 01:11:41,195
Ali claims he cannot be drafted
for religious reasons,

1231
01:11:41,197 --> 01:11:44,999
and now the high court will
decide whether he's right.

1232
01:11:45,001 --> 01:11:46,301
Is your client a pacifist?

1233
01:11:46,303 --> 01:11:50,038
A pacifist is, uh... is...
is, uh, strict language.

1234
01:11:50,040 --> 01:11:53,641
A pacifist means, um...
uh, a Quaker,

1235
01:11:53,643 --> 01:11:57,545
<i>one who does not engage
in any kind of violence.</i>

1236
01:11:57,547 --> 01:12:00,715
<i>It would hardly classify
him as a pacifist.</i>

1237
01:12:00,717 --> 01:12:03,618
Of course there's this
incredible irony...

1238
01:12:03,620 --> 01:12:10,591
that you have this big, powerful
heavyweight champion of the world...

1239
01:12:10,593 --> 01:12:13,995
<i>saying he's a
conscientious objector.</i>

1240
01:12:14,997 --> 01:12:18,733
<i>Justice Thurgood Marshall
recused himself from the case.</i>

1241
01:12:18,735 --> 01:12:21,102
He was largely removing
himself from any case...

1242
01:12:21,104 --> 01:12:23,504
<i>where the N.A.A.C.P.
Legal Defense Fund,</i>

1243
01:12:23,506 --> 01:12:26,808
<i>of which he used to be the head,
was representing a party.</i>

1244
01:12:26,810 --> 01:12:29,210
<i>The fact that Marshall
was not in the case...</i>

1245
01:12:29,212 --> 01:12:30,812
meant there were
only eight justices.

1246
01:12:30,814 --> 01:12:36,617
<i>So there was always the risk that
this case would come out 4-4.</i>

1247
01:12:36,619 --> 01:12:42,323
If the justices vote 4-4, the
decision below is affirmed.

1248
01:12:42,325 --> 01:12:44,892
<i>Ali would go to jail.</i>

1249
01:12:44,894 --> 01:12:48,162
<i>(MAN) Earlier this year Ali
began retempering the steel...</i>

1250
01:12:48,164 --> 01:12:51,866
<i>that lay beneath the starchy
lecture-circuit lunches.</i>

1251
01:12:51,868 --> 01:12:53,101
<i>(ALI)</i>
<i>All this is to me is a job.</i>

1252
01:12:53,103 --> 01:12:57,372
It means that I have a chance to earn
a living and take care of my family.

1253
01:12:57,374 --> 01:12:59,607
That's all it means to me.

1254
01:12:59,729 --> 01:13:01,809
<i>(ANNOUNCER)</i>
<i>In exhibitions like this,</i>

1255
01:13:01,811 --> 01:13:05,012
<i>sometimes he floated like
a butterfly in galoshes.</i>

1256
01:13:05,014 --> 01:13:07,648
<i>But there were moments
when a live youth...</i>

1257
01:13:07,650 --> 01:13:11,052
<i>broke through the
Rusty layers.</i>

1258
01:13:11,916 --> 01:13:14,756
<i>(ALI) Many critics
say it's impossible...</i>

1259
01:13:14,758 --> 01:13:17,592
<i>for a man to be off three
years and a half...</i>

1260
01:13:17,594 --> 01:13:18,693
<i>and with a six-week
notice be in shape.</i>

1261
01:13:18,695 --> 01:13:25,767
<i>It's impossible for him to have his wind,
his timing, his speed and his legs.</i>

1262
01:13:25,769 --> 01:13:27,969
<i>People are wondering
what can I do,</i>

1263
01:13:27,971 --> 01:13:32,907
<i>and we won't know until
the pressure's put on me.</i>

1264
01:13:33,075 --> 01:13:35,243
<i>(MAN) A man should be
entitled to do his job.</i>

1265
01:13:35,245 --> 01:13:38,746
He was convicted of a felony,
but he's not in jail.

1266
01:13:38,748 --> 01:13:40,314
And as long as he's free,

1267
01:13:40,316 --> 01:13:44,652
<i>he should be entitled
to make his living.</i>

1268
01:13:48,590 --> 01:13:53,094
<i>(ANNOUNCER) Win or lose, he's got the
appeal of his conviction to worry about...</i>

1269
01:13:53,096 --> 01:13:56,764
<i>and the possibility of
five years in prison.</i>

1270
01:13:56,766 --> 01:13:59,300
(GRUNTING)

1271
01:14:03,445 --> 01:14:04,205
Time!

1272
01:14:04,207 --> 01:14:07,408
<i>(KRATTENMAKER) When the case
was argued to the justices,</i>

1273
01:14:07,410 --> 01:14:10,411
<i>almost all the analysis
turned on the question...</i>

1274
01:14:10,413 --> 01:14:13,347
of whether he was a selective
conscientious objector.

1275
01:14:13,349 --> 01:14:19,187
That is, he had a conscientious objection
to this war but not another one.

1276
01:14:19,189 --> 01:14:23,257
<i>There is in this record
a basis, in fact,</i>

1277
01:14:23,259 --> 01:14:24,659
<i>for the conclusion...</i>

1278
01:14:24,661 --> 01:14:27,161
<i>that the petitioner's
objection,</i>

1279
01:14:27,163 --> 01:14:29,464
<i>though religious,
is selective.</i>

1280
01:14:29,466 --> 01:14:31,799
- <i>As-salaam alaikum.</i>
- <i>Wa as-salaam.</i>

1281
01:14:31,801 --> 01:14:34,902
<i>(GRISWOLD) That he is, in
fact, oppose to fighting...</i>

1282
01:14:34,904 --> 01:14:37,638
<i>what he regards as "the
white man's wars,"</i>

1283
01:14:37,640 --> 01:14:41,943
<i>although having no religious
or conscientious scruples...</i>

1284
01:14:41,945 --> 01:14:44,045
<i>against participation
in war...</i>

1285
01:14:44,047 --> 01:14:47,982
<i>which would defend the
black man's interests.</i>

1286
01:14:48,951 --> 01:14:51,419
The court voted
5-3 against Ali.

1287
01:14:51,421 --> 01:14:53,955
<i>It was all over
but the writing.</i>

1288
01:14:53,957 --> 01:15:00,495
<i>Metaphorically, Ali had one
foot and three toes in prison.</i>

1289
01:15:18,013 --> 01:15:23,284
<i>The Chief justice assigned the
opinion to Justice Harlan.</i>

1290
01:15:23,418 --> 01:15:28,856
<i>Justice Harlan... he was in very
good health, with one exception.</i>

1291
01:15:28,858 --> 01:15:29,891
<i>His eyesight was horrible.</i>

1292
01:15:29,893 --> 01:15:34,395
<i>He had had something that was
like a stroke of the eyes.</i>

1293
01:15:34,763 --> 01:15:40,034
<i>Part of the job of being Justice
Harlan's law clerk was to read to him.</i>

1294
01:15:40,036 --> 01:15:41,335
<i>And I told Justice Harlan...</i>

1295
01:15:41,337 --> 01:15:43,938
I might have said it more times
than is really polite...

1296
01:15:43,940 --> 01:15:48,175
<i>"When you go back and you read The
Message to the Blackman... ".</i>

1297
01:15:48,177 --> 01:15:50,511
Every one of you should have
this book in your study.

1298
01:15:50,513 --> 01:15:53,848
"And you read The
Autobiography of Malcolm X,"

1299
01:15:53,850 --> 01:15:55,416
the Nation of Islam
people were saying...

1300
01:15:55,418 --> 01:15:58,386
if Allah summons us to war,
then we will go to war.

1301
01:15:58,388 --> 01:16:02,023
If you really took the
law literally seriously,

1302
01:16:02,025 --> 01:16:07,361
<i>you cannot distinguish Jehovah's
Witnesses from the Nation of Islam...</i>

1303
01:16:07,363 --> 01:16:09,263
<i>"on this particular issue."</i>

